{
  "texts": [
    "Researchers often choose the WoS database for various reasons (Yong & Yuanqin, 2019; Yue et al., 2021; Atsiz et al., 2022), including its reputation as a leader among scientific databases with high-rated journals (Mergio et al., 2015; Mavric et al., 2021) and high quality (Hassan et al., 2022).",
    "In addition, one database is used to avoid duplicity (Mavric et al., 2021).",
    "A key-based methodology was utilized for the search process.",
    "The primary step of the search strategy involves identification of keywords and constructing an appropriate search query.",
    "The search query was based on the topic field (TS), which included records within title, abstract and author keywords (keywords that were identified by an author) and Keywords plus (index terms automatically generated from the titles of cited articles)."
  ]
}